        <div class="main-container">
          <p>Tic-Tac-Toe is a simple two-player game played on a 3×3 grid. Players take turns marking a space with either an <b>X</b> or an <b>O</b>. The first player to get three of their marks in a row (vertically, horizontally, or diagonally) wins!</p>
          <h4>Game Setup</h4>
          <ul>
              <li>The game is played on a 3×3 grid.</li>
              <li>One player is assigned <b>X</b> and the other <b>O</b>.</li>
              <li>Players take turns placing their symbol in an empty square.</li>
          </ul>
          <h4>How to Win</h4>
          <ul>
              <li>A player wins if they place three of their marks in a row (vertically, horizontally, or diagonally).</li>
              <li>If all nine squares are filled and no one has won, the game is a <b>draw</b>.</li>
          </ul>
          <h4>Basic Strategy</h4>
          <ul>
              <li>Try to get three in a row before your opponent.</li>
              <li>Block your opponent from getting three in a row.</li>
              <li>Control the center square for the best strategic advantage.</li>
          </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="footer">Enjoy your game and have fun!</div>
      </div>

      <script>
        const modal = document.getElementById('modal-con');
        const modalBtn = document.getElementById('modal-btn');
        const cancleBtn = document.getElementById('cancle-btn');
        const body = document.querySelector('body');
        let visible = false;
        console.log(cancleBtn)
        cancleBtn.onclick = ()=>{
          if(visible) {
            modal.style.display = 'none';
            visible = false

          }
        }
       
        modalBtn.onclick = ()=>{
         if(!visible){
           modal.style.display = 'flex';
           visible = true
         };
        }
      </script>
    
